Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a self-backhaul scheme for small cell networks, which involves the use of cellular communication technology. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates the power allocation problem of the MBS and SBSs as an optimization problem, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper proposes a scheme for dynamic resource allocation in next generation cellular networks, which involves the use of communication technologies. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for self-backhaul in small cell networks, which involves the use of control techniques to optimize the power allocation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper proposes a scheme for resource allocation in cellular networks, which may involve the transmission of multimedia content.
